#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:2
msgid "Performs a (local) reduce with specified slices over a single axis."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:4
msgid ""
"For i in ``range(len(indices))``, `reduceat` computes ``ufunc."
"reduce(array[indices[i]:indices[i+1]])``, which becomes the i-th generalized "
"\"row\" parallel to `axis` in the final result (i.e., in a 2-D array, for "
"example, if `axis = 0`, it becomes the i-th row, but if `axis = 1`, it "
"becomes the i-th column).  There are three exceptions to this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:10
msgid ""
"when ``i = len(indices) - 1`` (so for the last index), ``indices[i+1] = "
"array.shape[axis]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:12
msgid ""
"if ``indices[i] >= indices[i + 1]``, the i-th generalized \"row\" is simply "
"``array[indices[i]]``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:14
msgid ""
"if ``indices[i] >= len(array)`` or ``indices[i] < 0``, an error is raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.ufunc.reduceat:16
msgid ""
"The shape of the output depends on the size of `indices`, and may be larger "
"than `array` (this happens if ``len(indices) > array.shape[axis]``)."
msgstr ""

